{"parentUuid":"5c328e4a-cb3e-43a3-8968-421db8aea271","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"2e8aac70-7083-46be-b97a-0325443201fe","version":"2.1.39","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a6a2b94","slug":"happy-baking-hartmanis","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"<teammate-message teammate_id=\"carson-gross\" color=\"purple\" summary=\"BLOCKING still open: filter links need HTMX attrs for partial swap\">\nCarson here with re-review. I see good improvements (context grouping with sections/headings, pre-selected context in the select, wrapper div for the list). However:\n\n**BLOCKING -- still open:**\n\nThe filter links in `next_actions.html` (lines 17-28) still lack explicit HTMX attributes. They are plain `<a>` tags relying on hx-boost for full-page reload. My original blocking concern is not resolved.\n\nThe fix is now even simpler because the `<div id=\"next-actions-list\">` wrapper (line 66) already exists. The filter links just need HTMX attributes added. Here's what the \"All\" link should look like:\n\n```html\n<a href=\"/next-actions\"\n   hx-get=\"/next-actions\"\n   hx-target=\"#next-actions-list\"\n   hx-select=\"#next-actions-list\"\n   hx-swap=\"outerHTML\"\n   hx-push-url=\"true\"\n   {% if selected_context.is_none() %} aria-current=\"true\" class=\"next-actions__filter-link next-actions__filter-link--active\"{% else %} class=\"next-actions__filter-link\"{% endif %}>All</a>\n```\n\nAnd each context link:\n```html\n<a href=\"/next-actions?context={{ ctx.id }}\"\n   hx-get=\"/next-actions?context={{ ctx.id }}\"\n   hx-target=\"#next-actions-list\"\n   hx-select=\"#next-actions-list\"\n   hx-swap=\"outerHTML\"\n   hx-push-url=\"true\"\n   {% if selected_context.as_deref() == Some(ctx.id.as_str()) %} aria-current=\"true\" class=\"next-actions__filter-link next-actions__filter-link--active\"{% else %} class=\"next-actions__filter-link\"{% endif %}>{{ ctx.name }}</a>\n```\n\nThis works because:\n1. `hx-get` makes the request via HTMX instead of full navigation\n2. The server returns the full page (no backend changes needed)\n3. `hx-select=\"#next-actions-list\"` extracts just the action list div from the response\n4. `hx-target=\"#next-actions-list\"` + `hx-swap=\"outerHTML\"` replaces the current list with the filtered one\n5. `hx-push-url=\"true\"` updates the browser URL so the filter state is bookmarkable and back-button works\n6. The plain `href` remains as the no-JS fallback\n\nOne consideration: when `hx-select` pulls `#next-actions-list` from the response, the empty state div (`#next-actions-empty-state`) is *outside* that wrapper, so it won't update. You could either:\n(a) Move the empty state inside `#next-actions-list` (simplest), or\n(b) Expand the wrapper to include both\n\nI'd recommend (a) -- move the empty state div inside `#next-actions-list` so it gets swapped along with the list content. Then the empty state logic is fully server-driven during filter swaps.\n\n**Minor -- still open:**\nCancel link in `next_action_edit.html` (line 22) still lacks `aria-label=\"Cancel editing {{ action.title }}\"`.\n\nEverything else looks good. Once these two items are fixed, I'll give consensus approval.\n</teammate-message>"},"uuid":"0fda330e-4123-4f6c-9311-4debe1584d89","timestamp":"2026-02-12T23:38:27.400Z"}
